commitResults.messageBody:
Doctor class and Patient class have some common attributes (e.g Name
and NRIC) and common behaviours (e.g isSamePerson).

The common behaviours across Doctor and Patient classes cause code
duplication.

Extracting the common behavior into a super class allows us to use
polymorphism when dealing with patients and doctors.

Let's make the Person class abstract and let the Doctor and Patient
classes extend from Person.

Also added the Gender and Ic classes as fields in the Person class
which both Doctors and Patients have in common.

commitResults.messageBody:
Patient is a subtype of a person and can hence inherit from Person class
and its behaviours.

Creating a patient class along with two additional classes, Condition
and BloodType, which are stored in the patient class, allows us to
abstract different types of people in the system into classes.

Let's make the patient class extend the person class and have it
contain Condition and BloodType so that more information pertaining
to a patient can be stored.

We will add Doctor as a field in the patient class once the Doctor class
is fully implemented.

commitResults.messageBody:
Modified DeleteCommand and DeleteCommandParser classes to delete person
with specified nric, instead of previously which was deleting based on
index. Modified test cases to check for correct deletion based on nric
as well.

Made changes to several other test cases to accomodate for new
isSamePerson method which checks for same nric instead of same name.

Created GenderTest and IcTest unit tests for the Gender and Ic classes
respectively.

Made the following changes:

1. Added a header to each list
2. Changed HBox in the fxml file to ensure scrolling works
3. Corrected small typo in emergency contact field in card
4. Removed Name: in the card for the person's name for aesthetic
purposes

The command currently does not work still. There is an issue with the
copying of Files which the rest can hopefully figure out.

Here is how the command works:
When new command is added, model.saveToFile is called which will copy
the current file into the previous file.
When undo command is called, model.setToPreviousFile is called which
will copy the previous file into the current file, hence "reverting"
the changes.
